review_blob: pours amber with large off white head with good lacing.  faint aroma of coffee and chocolate.  low carbonation, watery,  tastes of chocolate and has some floral notes and is a bit sweet.  not bad
pours golden with minimal white head.  faint floral aroma. watery, low carbonation, a bit citrusy.  metallic finish.
pours golden with a big foamy head.  aroma of yeast and hops.  high carbonation, good lacing, bitter, tastes of grain and some fruit. good beer
pours amber with minimal head.  aroma of fruit and malt.  slick feel, taste is fruit and a bit nutty.  not bad

poured from bottle, appears amber with foamy head.  aroma is of grass and hops.  good lacing and light carbonation, very bitter, strong hoppiness, earthy and floral notes.  hoppy finish.  very good beer
pours golden with foamy white head.  very light malty aroma.  thin, tastes watery, overall boring beer
pours black with fast disappearing head.  aroma is dark chocolate and coffee.  full bodied, almost non-existent carbonation, tasting of dark chocolate and roasted malts.  smooth finish. awesome beer
malty aroma. light bodied tasting of caramel, toffee, and cereal.  dry finish.
from the bottle.  malty aroma.  medium carb, bitter,  tasting of grain and hops.  hoppy finish.
pours a clear gold with a small head. very light aroma of grass.  thin and watery with medium carbonation tasting of citrus and some floral notes.  the finish was a bit metallic.
pours a hazy gold with a frothy white head.  aroma of hops and some floral notes.  tastes citrusy with some spice and alcohol with high carbonation.  very good beer

pours a hazy amber with a small head.  floral aroma.  tastes nutty and citrus with a smooth finish.  good beer
pours amber with small head.  floral and nutty aroma.  light to medium  bodied, medium carbonation. tastes nutty with a bit of spice and honey.  good beer

amber appearance with very small head.  lemony aroma.  a bit sweet, hoppy with citrus notes, bitter finish.  would definitely have again
faint floral aroma, watered down and boring with a metallic finish.  very weak beer
clear golden appearance with minimal white head.  very light floral aroma.  mildly carbonated with a faint citrus taste and a slightly metallic finish.  decent beer.
golden appearance with minimal white head.  faintly hoppy aroma.  watered down, slightly metallic finish. not much else going on. boring and weak beer.
appears dark brown with minimal head.  aroma is roasted malt.  a bit  hoppy with a creamy texture tasting of dark chocolate and coffee.  slightly bitter finish.  good beer.
appearance is amber with a minimal white head.  nutty aroma and a bit hoppy with medium carbonation.  good beer.
clear golden appearance with minimal white head.  light bodied and oily texture, a bit sweet, no finish.  meh

roasty malt aroma, dark brown appearance, frothy head, full body, soft carbonation, smooth.
bottle.  malty aroma.  pours dark brown with thick brownish head.  tastes of dark chocolate and coffee. very smooth with low carbonation.  very good beer.
light and crisp, easy to drink and very refreshing.  readily available and inexpensive, my beer of choice to bring to parties.

1 pint bottle.  malty aroma.  hazy golden appearance with frothy head which disappears almost immediately.  lightly carbonated with oily texture.  very faint floral notes. metallic finish.  nothing remarkable.  probably wouldnt get this beer again.
1 pint bottle.  very light aroma of grass. pale golden beer with high carbonation and a decent white head. very light, smooth to drink.  metallic finish. decent beer.
